{"bookResponse":{"bookId":"2ad4ecbb8e24f6cd9efcac897a233cf2","locale":"en_US","title":"macOS User Guide","meta":{"productVersion":"13.0","platformOSVersion":"13.0","icon":"https://help.apple.com/assets/63BCA927AAE78C58DD7FBE35/63BCA92EAAE78C58DD7FBE76/en_US/058e4af8e726290f491044219d2eee73.png","build_date":"Wed Mar 22 20:19:57 GMT 2023","product":"mac-help","creationDate":"Fri Mar 24 07:00:00 GMT 2023","lastModifiedDate":"Mon Mar 27 17:01:20 GMT 2023","contentType":"book","framework":"duck-15.4.0:goose-2.15.4:cuckoo-4.2.0"},"tocId":"MH43558","bookInfo":{"versionsDetails":[{"productVersion":"14.0","displayVersion":"macOS Sonoma 14","platform":"mac","platformOSVersion":"14.0"},{"productVersion":"13.0","displayVersion":"macOS Ventura 13","platform":"mac","platformOSVersion":"13.0"},{"productVersion":"12.0","displayVersion":"macOS Monterey 12","platform":"mac","platformOSVersion":"12.0"},{"productVersion":"11.0","displayVersion":"macOS Big Sur 11.0","platform":"mac","platformOSVersion":"11.0"},{"productVersion":"10.15","displayVersion":"macOS Catalina 10.15","platform":"mac","platformOSVersion":"10.15"},{"productVersion":"10.14","displayVersion":"macOS Mojave 10.14","platform":"mac","platformOSVersion":"10.14"},{"productVersion":"10.13","displayVersion":"macOS High Sierra","platform":"mac","platformOSVersion":"10.13"}]},"articles":[{"articleId":{"id":"BK_2AD4ECBB8E24F6CD9EFCAC897A233CF2_MH26684","locale":"en_US"},"meta":{"createDate":"Fri Mar 24 07:00:00 GMT 2023","lastModifiedDate":"Mon Mar 27 17:01:20 GMT 2023","publishedDate":"Mon Mar 27 17:01:20 GMT 2023","contentType":"book","archive":"false","ownerName":"apd migration","modifiedBy":"apd migration","version":"1","unPublished":false,"contentModel":"book"},"content":{"main":{"title":"Change the language your Mac uses","summary":"On your Mac, change the language shown in menus and dialogs and in many apps."},"sections":[{"level":"1","text":"<body dir=\"ltr\" id=\"mh26684\" class=\"AppleTopic apd-topic dark-mode-enabled\" data-istaskopen=\"true\" data-designversion=\"2\" lang=\"en\"><a name=\"mh26684\"></a><figure class=\"topicIcon\"><img src=\"https://help.apple.com/assets/63BCA927AAE78C58DD7FBE35/63BCA92EAAE78C58DD7FBE76/en_US/cf3ba3fdc113331630873abc2db855e3.png\" alt=\"\" height=\"30\" width=\"30\" originalImageName=\"SharedGlobalArt/AppIconTopic_Localization.png\"></figure><h1>Change the language your Mac uses</h1><p>Although your Mac is set to display the language of the country or region in which it was purchased, you can choose a different language to use. For example, if you bought your Mac in the United States but you work primarily in French, you can set your Mac to use French.</p><p>You can also choose different languages for individual apps. For example, if your system language is set to Simplified Chinese, but you prefer to use a certain app in English, you can do so.</p><div id=\"mchlp6f578d0\" class=\"Task\"><h2 aria-controls=\"aria-mchlp6f578d0\" class=\"Name\">Change the system language</h2><div class=\"TaskBody\" role=\"region\" aria-hidden=\"false\" id=\"aria-mchlp6f578d0\"><ol><li><p>On your Mac, choose Apple menu <picture><source media=\"(not all)\" srcset=\"https://help.apple.com/assets/63BCA927AAE78C58DD7FBE35/63BCA92EAAE78C58DD7FBE76/en_US/0e2c53fa5a413cc7ff5099226fb50188.png\" originalImageName=\"SharedGlobalArt/IL_AppleLogo_11~dark.png\"></source><img src=\"https://help.apple.com/assets/63BCA927AAE78C58DD7FBE35/63BCA92EAAE78C58DD7FBE76/en_US/2f77cc85238452e25cb517130188bf99.png\" alt=\"\" height=\"30\" width=\"24\" originalImageName=\"SharedGlobalArt/IL_AppleLogo_11.png\"></picture> &gt; System Settings, click General <img src=\"https://help.apple.com/assets/63BCA927AAE78C58DD7FBE35/63BCA92EAAE78C58DD7FBE76/en_US/7c4faef8373d3d73052729c76d485046.png\" alt=\"\" height=\"30\" width=\"30\" originalImageName=\"SharedGlobalArt/AppIconTopic_General.png\"> in the sidebar, then click Language &amp; Region on the right. (You may need to scroll down.)</p><p><a href=\"x-help-action://openPrefPane?bundleId=com.apple.Localization-Settings.extension\" class=\"URL\">Open Language &amp; Region settings for me</a></p></li><li><p>Under Preferred Languages, do any of the following:</p><ul><li><p><em>Add a language: </em>Click the Add button <span class=\"NoBreak\"><img src=\"https://help.apple.com/assets/63BCA927AAE78C58DD7FBE35/63BCA92EAAE78C58DD7FBE76/en_US/a2ef32e34a5573d192b10d340a4f46b1.png\" alt=\"\" height=\"30\" width=\"30\" originalImageName=\"SharedGlobalArt/IL_Plus.png\">, </span>select one or more languages in the list, then click Add.</p><p>The list is divided by a separator line. Languages above the line are system languages that are fully supported by macOS and are shown in menus, notifications, websites, and more. Languages below the line aren’t fully supported by macOS, but may be supported by apps that you use, and on some websites.</p><p>If you can’t use the input source that’s selected in the <a href=\"https://support.apple.com/guide/?platform=mac&amp;product=mac-help&amp;vanityname=input-menu&amp;version=13.0&amp;locale=en_US&amp;topicid=GLOS52ED78A0&amp;type=ddm&amp;platformOSVersion=13.0&amp;aside=true\" class=\"xRef Aside\">Input menu</a> to type a selected language, a list of available sources is shown. If you don’t add an input source now, you can <a href=\"https://support.apple.com/guide/?platform=mac&amp;product=mac-help&amp;vanityname=write-in-another-language-on-mac&amp;version=13.0&amp;locale=en_US&amp;topicid=MCHLP1406&amp;type=ddm&amp;platformOSVersion=13.0#mchlpa10dc0f\" class=\"xRef Task\">add it</a> later in Keyboard settings.</p></li><li><p><em>Change the primary language: </em>Drag a language to the top of the languages list.</p><div class=\"Alert\"><p class=\"Note\"><em>Note: </em>You may need to restart your Mac to see the change in all applications.</p></div><p>If macOS or an app supports the primary language, menus and notifications are shown in that language. If it doesn’t, it uses the next language in the list, and so on. The language may also be used on websites that support it.</p><p>The order of the languages in the list determines how text appears when you type characters in a script that belongs to more than one language. See <a href=\"https://support.apple.com/guide/?platform=mac&amp;product=mac-help&amp;vanityname=latin-fonts-correctly-mac&amp;version=13.0&amp;locale=en_US&amp;topicid=MCHL14CC6599&amp;type=ddm&amp;platformOSVersion=13.0\" class=\"xRef AppleTopic\">If non-Latin fonts don’t appear correctly</a>.</p></li></ul></li></ol><p>If your Mac <a href=\"https://support.apple.com/guide/?platform=mac&amp;product=mac-help&amp;vanityname=change-users-groups-settings&amp;version=13.0&amp;locale=en_US&amp;topicid=MTUSR001&amp;type=ddm&amp;platformOSVersion=13.0\" class=\"xRef AppleTopic\">has multiple users</a> and you want everyone to see the language you chose as the primary language in the login window, click the Settings pop-up menu <span class=\"NoBreak\"><img src=\"https://help.apple.com/assets/63BCA927AAE78C58DD7FBE35/63BCA92EAAE78C58DD7FBE76/en_US/5b4ea84bccf6930b115b8d113b5e3016.png\" alt=\"\" height=\"30\" width=\"30\" originalImageName=\"SharedGlobalArt/IL_Gear.png\">, </span>then choose Apply to Login Window. (If the Settings pop-up menu doesn’t appear, it means the login window is already set to use the primary language.)</p></div></div><div id=\"mchlf6cd6fbc\" class=\"Task\"><h2 aria-controls=\"aria-mchlf6cd6fbc\" class=\"Name\">Choose the language you use for individual apps</h2><div class=\"TaskBody\" role=\"region\" aria-hidden=\"false\" id=\"aria-mchlf6cd6fbc\"><ol><li><p>On your Mac, choose Apple menu <picture><source media=\"(not all)\" srcset=\"https://help.apple.com/assets/63BCA927AAE78C58DD7FBE35/63BCA92EAAE78C58DD7FBE76/en_US/0e2c53fa5a413cc7ff5099226fb50188.png\" originalImageName=\"SharedGlobalArt/IL_AppleLogo_11~dark.png\"></source><img src=\"https://help.apple.com/assets/63BCA927AAE78C58DD7FBE35/63BCA92EAAE78C58DD7FBE76/en_US/2f77cc85238452e25cb517130188bf99.png\" alt=\"\" height=\"30\" width=\"24\" originalImageName=\"SharedGlobalArt/IL_AppleLogo_11.png\"></picture> &gt; System Settings, click General <img src=\"https://help.apple.com/assets/63BCA927AAE78C58DD7FBE35/63BCA92EAAE78C58DD7FBE76/en_US/7c4faef8373d3d73052729c76d485046.png\" alt=\"\" height=\"30\" width=\"30\" originalImageName=\"SharedGlobalArt/AppIconTopic_General.png\"> in the sidebar, then click Language &amp; Region on the right. (You may need to scroll down.)</p><p><a href=\"x-help-action://openPrefPane?bundleId=com.apple.Localization-Settings.extension\" class=\"URL\">Open Language &amp; Region settings for me</a></p></li><li><p>Go to Applications, then do any of the following:</p><ul><li><p><em>Choose a language for an app: </em>Click the Add button <span class=\"NoBreak\"><img src=\"https://help.apple.com/assets/63BCA927AAE78C58DD7FBE35/63BCA92EAAE78C58DD7FBE76/en_US/a2ef32e34a5573d192b10d340a4f46b1.png\" alt=\"\" height=\"30\" width=\"30\" originalImageName=\"SharedGlobalArt/IL_Plus.png\">, </span>choose an app and a language from the pop-up menus, then click Add.</p></li><li><p><em>Change the language for an app in the list: </em>Select the app, then choose a new language from the pop-up menu.</p></li><li><p><em>Remove an app from the list: </em>Select the app, then click the Remove button <span class=\"NoBreak\"><img src=\"https://help.apple.com/assets/63BCA927AAE78C58DD7FBE35/63BCA92EAAE78C58DD7FBE76/en_US/e9a8ab65e535ed110ae953650c55ee0c.png\" alt=\"\" height=\"30\" width=\"29\" originalImageName=\"SharedGlobalArt/IL_Minus.png\">. </span>The app uses the default language again.</p></li></ul></li></ol><p>If the app is open, you may need to close and then reopen it to see the change.</p></div></div><div class=\"LinkUniversal\"><strong>See also</strong><a href=\"https://support.apple.com/guide/?platform=mac&amp;product=mac-help&amp;vanityname=write-in-another-language-on-mac&amp;version=13.0&amp;locale=en_US&amp;topicid=MCHLP1406&amp;type=ddm&amp;platformOSVersion=13.0\" class=\"xRef AppleTopic\">Write in another language on Mac</a><a href=\"https://support.apple.com/guide/?platform=mac&amp;product=mac-help&amp;vanityname=check-spelling-and-grammar-on-mac&amp;version=13.0&amp;locale=en_US&amp;topicid=MCHLP2299&amp;type=ddm&amp;platformOSVersion=13.0\" class=\"xRef AppleTopic\">Check spelling and grammar on Mac</a></div></body>","tags":[{"type":"audience","refKey":"PUBLIC_USERS","tagPath":"audience/PUBLIC_USERS","title":"Public"}]}]},"categoryInfo":{"categories":["IP-Meta/DesignVersion/DesignVersion2","platform/mac","DisplayVersion/macOS Ventura 13","MetaFollow/MetaFollowOFF","ContentMode/liveContent","SupportSearchIndex/SupportSearchIndexON","ArchivalStatus/Archived","ExternalIndex/ExternalIndexOFF"],"categoryDictionaries":[{"key":"SupportSearchIndexON","name":"SupportSearchIndexON","englishName":"SupportSearchIndexON","displayName":"SupportSearchIndexON","articleCount":"120736"},{"key":"liveContent","name":"Live Content","englishName":"Live Content","displayName":"Live Content","articleCount":"135880"},{"key":"IP-Meta","name":"IP-Meta","englishName":"IP-Meta","displayName":"IP-Meta","articleCount":"0"},{"key":"ContentMode","name":"ContentMode","englishName":"ContentMode","displayName":"ContentMode","articleCount":"0"},{"key":"DesignVersion2","name":"DesignVersion 2","englishName":"DesignVersion 2","displayName":"DesignVersion 2","articleCount":"135315"},{"key":"MetaFollow","name":"MetaFollow","englishName":"MetaFollow","displayName":"MetaFollow","articleCount":"0"},{"key":"ExternalIndex","name":"ExternalIndex","englishName":"ExternalIndex","displayName":"ExternalIndex","articleCount":"0"},{"key":"DesignVersion","name":"DesignVersion","englishName":"DesignVersion","displayName":"DesignVersion","articleCount":"0"},{"key":"platform","name":"platform","englishName":"platform","displayName":"platform","articleCount":"0"},{"key":"mac","name":"mac","englishName":"mac","dis